# PDF Search Skill (sova)

Search your indexed PDF documents using semantic search.

## When to Use

- Looking up information in reference documents
- Finding relevant sections across multiple PDFs
- Verifying facts or quotes from source materials

## Search

```bash
cd /path/to/sova

# Semantic search (returns file:line-range with preview)
uv run sova.py -s "your search query"
uv run sova.py -s "query" -n 10  # More results

# Text search (exact matches)
rg -i "keyword" *.md
```

Returns `file.md:start-end` with preview. Use Read tool for full context (add ~50 lines buffer for surrounding context):

```bash
# Search returns: mybook.md:580-650 (0.68)
# Read with context buffer
```

```
Read /path/to/sova/mybook.md lines 530-700
```

## Setup

If the database doesn't exist or is incomplete:

```bash
cd /path/to/sova

# Create symlink to PDFs (if not exists)
ln -s /path/to/docs docs

# Check status
uv run sova.py --list

# Index all PDFs (embeddings only, faster)
uv run sova.py --skip-topics

# Or with topic extraction (slower)
uv run sova.py
```

Requires Ollama running with:
- `qwen3-embedding:8b` for embeddings
- `gemma3:12b` for topic extraction (optional)

## Adding Documents

Drop PDFs in the symlinked directory and re-run indexing:

```bash
uv run sova.py new-doc-name
```
